ggplot2: Facets

Agenda

Libraries

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)

Data

ecom <- readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rsquaredacademy/datasets/master/web.csv')

Data Dictionary

  • id: row id
  • referrer: referrer website/search engine
  • os: operating system
  • browser: browser
  • device: device used to visit the website
  • n_pages: number of pages visited
  • duration: time spent on the website (in seconds)
  • repeat: frequency of visits
  • country: country of origin
  • purchase: whether visitor purchased
  • order_value: order value of visitor (in dollars)

Facet - Intro

Generate subplots that each display one subset of the data using

  • facet_grid()
  • facet_wrap()

Columns

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) + 
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(. ~ device)

Rows

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) + 
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(device ~ .)

Rows & Columns

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) + 
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(purchase ~ device)

Rows & Columns

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) + 
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(device ~ purchase)

Scales

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration, color = factor(device))) +
  geom_point() + 
  facet_grid(. ~ device, scales = "free")

Switch Axis

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  facet_grid(device ~ purchase, switch = "both")

Wrap

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~device)

Specify Rows

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~device, nrow = 2)

Specify Rows

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~device, nrow = 3)

Rows & Columns

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~device + purchase)

Rows & Columns

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(c("device", "purchase"))

Scales

ggplot(ecom, aes(n_pages, duration)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~device, scales = "free")
